            "en": "<ul><li>The company or establishment where the person aged 58 or over works must be located in the <strong>Flemish Region</strong>.</li><li>Your company must belong to the <strong>private sector</strong>, i.e. not to the government or social profit sector.</li><li>Your employee must be <strong>aged 58 or over</strong> on the last day of the quarter for which you are applying for the NSSO reduction.</li><li>As an entrepreneur, you can only receive the NSSO reduction if the <strong>reference quarter salary</strong> of the employee for whom you are requesting the reduction remains below the limit of EUR 13,945. The reference quarter salary is the gross salary that said employee earns when they work full-time and continuously during one quarter.</li><li>If the employee did not work full-time in a particular quarter, for example because they entered into employment in the middle of a quarter, or in the event of part-time work or long-term illness, the amount of the reduction will be adjusted.</li><li>Before hiring a <strong>new employee aged 58 or over</strong>, the potential employee must have <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/inschrijving-als-werkzoekende-bij-vdab\">registered in advance with the Flemish Service for Employment and Vocational Training </a>(Dutch: Vlaamse Dienst voor Arbeidsbemiddeling en Beroepsopleiding/VDAB). Specifically, the employee must have been registered as a non-working job seeker for at least 1 working day in the month preceding the new employment. E.g. someone who is hired on 10 October must have been registered for at least 1 day as a non-working job seeker in the period from 10 September through 9 October.</li><li>Employees <strong>who were already employed </strong>before the age of 58 do not have to register with VDAB.</li></ul>"
